network_overview: Trace contains only two micro-flows: a 3-packet TCP/HTTP exchange between RFC-1918 hosts and a single UDP packet likely carrying PFCP heartbeat. No mobile-specific signaling (GTP, Diameter, SIP, RTP) is present at this capture point.

observations.finding: Gi/SGi user-plane HTTP transaction completed in <2 ms with 1759 pkt/s burst rate
observations.evidence: Flow 1: 3 TCP segments (SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK) between 192.168.1.1:1234 ↔ 192.168.1.2:80, duration 1.7 ms

observations.finding: Single 53-byte UDP packet matches PFCP heartbeat size

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No SIP, RTP, or IMS protocols observed
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on N2/N3 or S1-U/S11 interfaces to expose SIP and RTP

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No GTP-C, PFCP session-mgmt, or Diameter messages present
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on N4, Sx, S5, or S11 control interfaces

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No Diameter S6a, Cx, or MAP traffic observed
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on Diameter routing agents or STP links

recommendations.action: Re-locate probe to upstream control interface (N4, Sx, S5, S11) to capture session-establishment signaling
recommendations.rationale: Current Gi/SGi vantage point only shows post-NAT user traffic; cannot determine bearer success or failure

recommendations.action: Filter and collect PFCP/UDP port 8805 messages for full N4/Sx heartbeat trend
recommendations.rationale: Observed 53-byte packet aligns with PFCP heartbeat size; continuous loss could indicate UPF/SMF path issues

session_analysis.signaling_health: Only one potential PFCP heartbeat observed; no session-level signaling visible
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Single HTTP transaction completed successfully with normal TCP handshake
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable at this capture point
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: No correlation possible: control and user planes captured on different flows with no shared identifiers
